data.body:
I'm aware that the JSON (and cson) data format doesn't include a way to serialize and deserialize Function objects.

Never-the-less, the `ContextMenuManager.add()` accepts an Object and supports some attributes that are expected to be a Function. By specifying the value of this Object in JSON, these (Function) attributes cannot be used.

What I propose is that "shouldDisplay" and "created" be allowed to be encoded as String values. These strings contain the body of each Function (respectively). If the attribute is defined and is a String, then it is passed to the Function constructor and the resulting Function be assigned to the Object attribute.

suggested position in source to insert additional code:

```coffeescript
# https://atom.io/docs/api/v1.1.0/ContextMenuManager#instance-add
# https://github.com/atom/atom/blob/v1.19.0-beta3/src/context-menu-manager.coffee#L57

map = CSON.readFileSync(platformMenuPath)

# insertion point

@add(map['context-menu'])
```

example (written in javascript. needs translation into coffeescript.)<br>
to illustrate what this new code might look like:

```javascript
// https://github.com/atom/season#csonreadfilesyncobjectpath
// https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function

for (let css_selector in map['context-menu']) {
  let items = map['context-menu'][css_selector]
  items.forEach((item, item_index) => {
    if (typeof item.shouldDisplay === 'string') {
      try {
        let shouldDisplay = new Function('event', item.shouldDisplay)
        // is the package an object that's in scope?
        // if so, bind "this" to package
        // allows the function to use the state of the package to determine visibility
        shouldDisplay = shouldDisplay.bind(@package)
        map['context-menu'][css_selector][item_index]['shouldDisplay'] = shouldDisplay
      }
      catch(error) {
        delete map['context-menu'][css_selector][item_index]['shouldDisplay']
      }
    }
    if (typeof item.created === 'string') {
      try {
        let created = new Function('event', item.created)
        // bind "this" to: item
        // allows the function to call: `this.label = 'foo'; this.command = 'bar:baz'`
        created = created.bind(map['context-menu'][css_selector][item_index])
        map['context-menu'][css_selector][item_index]['created'] = created
      }
      catch(error) {
        delete map['context-menu'][css_selector][item_index]['created']
      }
    }
  })
}
```

example "menus/*.cson" data file:

```cson
'context-menu':
  'atom-workspace': [
    {label: 'Help', command: 'application:open-documentation'},
    {shouldDisplay: 'return (!! this.is_visible) // where @is_visible belongs to the package', created: 'if (event.target.matches(".css.class")){this.label="Selective Helper"; this.command="application:open-special-documentation"} else{this.label="Default Helper"; this.command="application:open-default-documentation"}'}
  ]
```
